records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.   
Count 2 - Deliver Heroin - Guilty plea.  
Count 4 - Fleeing an Officer - Guilty plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 1, deliver cocaine within 1,000 feet of school and count 3, deliver cocaine.   Motion granted.    
Count 2 - Deliver Heroin - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of five (5) years.   Two (2) years initial confinement, followed by three (3) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Reimburse $240.00 buy money;
2) Obtain HSED/GED;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
5) Submit DNA sample;
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
8) AODA assessment and follow through; 
9) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
Count 4 - Fleeing an officer - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of three and one-half (3 1/2) years.   Eighteen (18) months initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Obtain HSED/GED;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
4) Submit DNA sample;
5) Pay costs of action;
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) AODA assessment and follow through;
8) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
9) Six (6) month driver's license suspension. 
Defendant is given credit for 175 days time already served.   
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for the Substance Abuse Program.  
Minutes.
